    {
      "number": 4,
      "id": "PR_kwDOP8SUQc7EbliN",
      "title": "-01 changes",
      "url": "https://github.com/yaroslavros/connect-ip-optimizations/pull/4",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "yaroslavros",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "* Separated templates and checksum offload\r\n* Added derived fields for lengths and complete checksums. Added IANA registry for derived fields (more stuff might be added in the future for other protocols)\r\n* Changed capsule design to include Next Context ID\r\n* Aligned ASSIGN/ACK/CLOSE capsule design and naming with other masque drafts\r\n* Templates are applicable to any HTTP datagram based protocols\r\n* CONNECT-ETHERNET can use same derived fields and checksum offload as CONNECT-IP\r\n* Added `mtu` and `segments` restrictions based on feedback from the working group\r\n\r\nKeeping the draft name as it is for now - will update it if working group decides to adopt this at some point in the future.\r\n\r\nIt seems that with all these optimisations sending Ethernet over HTTP/QUIC Datagrams might become viable - at least from MTU perspective!",
      "createdAt": "2026-02-17T18:42:06Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-02-26T22:50:42Z",
      "baseRepository": "yaroslavros/connect-ip-optimizations",
      "baseRefName": "main",
      "baseRefOid": "463a6cc3259ee6cd7a7982e420822bb853c66450",
      "headRepository": "yaroslavros/connect-ip-optimizations",
      "headRefName": "01",
      "headRefOid": "220120897ce42626d4637db15d33e9b880165828",
      "closedAt": "2026-02-26T22:50:42Z",
      "mergedAt": "2026-02-26T22:50:42Z",
      "mergedBy": "yaroslavros",
